profile_positions.description:
-Provide effective support to the CWtL programme teams in various countries; 
-Contribute to ensuring quality and accountability standards are met during programme implementation by providing project management and monitoring support, including the development and roll-out of project management tools which meet War Child Holland (WCH) and programme donor quality and accountability standards; 
-Support and train programme partners, where necessary, to maintain these standards; 
-Contribute technical expertise in education in emergencies and/or psychosocial support programming to programme partners in collaboration with the global CWtL programme team, which includes WCH and external partners. This will, in turn, support the CWtL programme ambitions to scale up in three – four countries from 2016 – 2020.
